.RE
.B
\fBconvertToGreyscale(This, Weight_r, Weight_g, Weight_b) ->\fR
\fB                            wxImage()\fR
\fB                            when\fR
\fB                                This :: wxImage(),\fR
\fB                                Weight_r :: number(),\fR
\fB                                Weight_g :: number(),\fR
\fB                                Weight_b :: number().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns a greyscale version of the image.

.PP
The returned image uses the luminance component of the original to calculate the greyscale. Defaults to using the standard ITU-T BT.601 when converting to YUV, where every pixel equals (R \fI \fIweight_r\fR) + (G \fR \fIweight_g\fR) + (B * \fIweight_b\fR).


