\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxIMAGE_OPTION_QUALITY:\fR JPEG quality used when saving. This is an integer in 0..100 range with 0 meaning very poor and 100 excellent (but very badly compressed). This option is currently ignored for the other formats.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxIMAGE_OPTION_RESOLUTIONUNIT:\fR The value of this option determines whether the resolution of the image is specified in centimetres or inches, see wxImageResolution enum elements.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxIMAGE_OPTION_RESOLUTION\fR, \fIwxIMAGE_OPTION_RESOLUTIONX\fR and \fIwxIMAGE_OPTION_RESOLUTIONY:\fR These options define the resolution of the image in the units corresponding to \fIwxIMAGE_OPTION_RESOLUTIONUNIT\fR options value. The first option can be set before saving the image to set both horizontal and vertical resolution to the same value. The X and Y options are set by the image handlers if they support the image resolution (currently BMP, JPEG and TIFF handlers do) and the image provides the resolution information and can be queried after loading the image.

